<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf688b830-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s9305"><num value="9305">§ 9305.</num><heading> Agreements with Canada</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">To provide for a coordinated system of pilotage service on the Great Lakes, the Secretary, subject to the concurrence of the Secretary of State, may make agreements with the appropriate agency of Canada to—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf688b831-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s9305/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> fix the number of pilots to be registered in each country;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf688b832-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s9305/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> provide for participation on an equitable basis;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf688b833-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s9305/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> prescribe joint or identical rates and charges;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf688b834-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s9305/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> coordinate pool operations; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf688b835-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s9305/5"><num value="5">(5)</num><content> establish conditions for services by registered pilots.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idf688b836-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/559">97 Stat. 559</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
